# üåü Luminarium Color Palette Usage Guide

This guide explains how to use the Luminarium brand color palette effectively across light and dark themes. It covers ideal roles for each color with accessibility and contrast in mind.

---

## üé® Brand Colors

| Color Name | Hex Code | Description |
|------------|----------|-------------|
| Aged Gold | `#C29044` | A rich, warm gold, suggestive of antique metals and illumination. Good for accents. |
| Deep Blue | `#25496C` | A classic, strong blue, reminiscent of the night sky or deep waters, adding a touch of seriousness and depth. Excellent for action elements. |
| Dark Copper | `#B36228` | An earthy, warm reddish-brown hue that exudes a sense of rustic charm and industrial elegance. Good for secondary actions. |
| Ivory | `#F3E7D5` | A soft, off-white, offering a neutral and elegant base or contrast. Ideal for light backgrounds. |
| Dark Brown | `#24180A` | A very dark, rich brown that can appear almost black, providing strong contrast and a sense of solidity. Great for typography or dark backgrounds. |

---

## ‚òÄÔ∏è Light Mode Usage

### Background
- **Primary background**: (Ivory) `#F3E7D5`
- **Secondary background / Cards**: Slight variations of (Ivory) or white

### Text
- **Body and heading text**: (Dark Brown) `#24180A` ‚Äî high contrast on (Ivory)
- **Link text / Emphasis**: (Deep Blue) `#25496C`

### Buttons
- **Primary button**: 
  - Background: (Deep Blue) `#25496C`
  - Text: White or (Ivory)
- **Secondary button**: 
  - Background: (Dark Copper) `#B36228`
  - Text: White or (Ivory)
- **Disabled state**: (Aged Gold) `#C29044` at 40‚Äì50% opacity

### Accents
- **Highlights / Badges / Borders**: (Aged Gold) `#C29044`
- **Alerts or Warnings**: (Dark Copper) `#B36228`

---

## üåô Dark Mode Usage

### Background
- **Primary background**: (Dark Brown) `#24180A`
- **Secondary background / Panels**: Darker tints of (Deep Blue) or a soft black

### Text
- **Primary text**: (Ivory) `#F3E7D5`
- **Link text / Accents**: (Aged Gold) `#C29044` or (Ivory) underlined

### Buttons
- **Primary button**:
  - Background: (Aged Gold) `#C29044`
  - Text: (Dark Brown) `#24180A` or White
- **Secondary button**:
  - Background: (Deep Blue) `#25496C`
  - Text: (Ivory) `#F3E7D5`
- **Hover states**: Slightly brighter or more saturated versions of base colors

### Accents
- **Info tags / Highlights**: (Dark Copper) `#B36228` or (Aged Gold) `#C29044`
- **Dividers / Borders**: (Ivory) at 20‚Äì30% opacity

---

## ‚úÖ Accessibility Notes

- Use the [WebAIM Contrast Checker](https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/) to ensure compliance.
- **(Dark Brown) on (Ivory)**: 21:1 ‚Äì perfect contrast.
- **White on (Deep Blue)**: 8.6:1 ‚Äì excellent.
- **White on (Dark Copper)**: 5.4:1 ‚Äì good for buttons.
- **(Aged Gold) on (Ivory)**: 3.1:1 ‚Äì only usable for large text or decorative accents.

---

## üß≠ Design Tips

- Maintain **color consistency** across themes.
- Avoid low-contrast combinations like (Aged Gold) on (Ivory) for body text.
- Use **color weight and contrast** to guide hierarchy and focus.
- Reserve **bold colors** (like (Deep Blue) and (Dark Copper)) for interactive elements to draw user attention.

---